      "content": "that's a good start. can u expand on the part about it being a 'moral imperative'? like, i want to argue that the current system isn't just inefficient, but actually fundamentally unjust because of how wealth was originally built. maybe add some points on why relying on 'meritocracy' is basically just a way to justify the status quo?",
